 evaluation using the generated rubrics and your dataset. The </span><code style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">evaluate</code><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> method of </span><code style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">EvalTask</code><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> will use the rubric validator to score the generated content.</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"eval_task = EvalTask(\n    dataset=dataset_with_rubrics,\n    metrics=[rubric_based_gecko],\n)\neval_result = eval_task.evaluate(response_column_name=&quot;image&quot;) # or &quot;video&quot;\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\">\n      lang-py\n     </div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-language=\"lang-py\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\" style=\"display: none;\">eval_task = EvalTask(\n    dataset=dataset_with_rubrics,\n    metrics=[rubric_based_gecko],\n)\neval_result = eval_task.evaluate(response_column_name=\"image\") # or \"video\"</textarea>\n       <div class=\"CodeMirror cm-s-default CodeMirror-wrap\" translate=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%;\">\n        <div style=\"overflow:hidden;top:4px;left:4px;width:3px;height:0px;\">\n         <textarea autocorrect=\"off\" autocapitalize=\"off\" spellcheck=\"false\" disabled readonly tabindex=\"0\" style=\"padding:0px;outline:none;bottom:-1em;width:100%;min-height:1em;height:1em;\"></textarea>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"CodeMirror-scroll\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-sizer\" style=\"margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: -15px; border-right-width: 35px; min-height: 204px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">\n          <div style=\"top:0px;\">\n           <div class=\"CodeMirror-lines\" role=\"presentation\">\n            <div role=\"presentation\" style=\"outline:none;\">\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-cursors\"></div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-code\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"\">\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">eval_task = EvalTask(</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"> &nbsp;  dataset=dataset_with_rubrics,</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"> &nbsp;  metrics=[rubric_based_gecko],</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">)</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">eval_result = eval_task.evaluate(response_column_name=\"image\") # or \"video\"</span></pre>\n              </div>\n             </div>\n            </div>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-gutters\" style=\"height: 239px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">After the evaluation runs, you can compute and analyze the final scores to understand how well your generated content aligns with the detailed criteria derived from your prompts.</span></p>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Python</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"dataset_with_final_scores = compute_scores(eval_result.metrics_table)\nnp.mean(dataset_with_final_scores[&quot;final_score&quot;])\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\" style=\"display: none;\">dataset_with_final_scores = compute_scores(eval_result.metrics_table)\nnp.mean(dataset_with_final_scores[\"final_score\"])</textarea>\n       <div class=\"CodeMirror cm-s-default CodeMirror-wrap\" translate=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%;\">\n        <div style=\"overflow:hidden;top:4px;left:4px;width:3px;height:0px;\">\n         <textarea autocorrect=\"off\" autocapitalize=\"off\" spellcheck=\"false\" disabled readonly tabindex=\"0\" style=\"padding:0px;outline:none;bottom:-1em;width:100%;min-height:1em;height:1em;\"></textarea>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"CodeMirror-scroll\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-sizer\" style=\"margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: -15px; border-right-width: 35px; min-height: 148px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">\n          <div style=\"top:0px;\">\n           <div class=\"CodeMirror-lines\" role=\"presentation\">\n            <div role=\"presentation\" style=\"outline:none;\">\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-cursors\"></div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-code\" role=\"presentation\">\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">dataset_with_final_scores = compute_scores(eval_result.metrics_table)</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">np.mean(dataset_with_final_scores[\"final_score\"])</span></pre>\n              </div>\n             </div>\n            </div>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-gutters\" style=\"height: 183px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Vertex AI Gen AI evaluation service offers summary and metrics tables, providing detailed insights into the evaluation performance. Beyond that, for Gecko you will find the category or concept which each of the questions is categorized as, as well as the score of the generated image or video performed against that category. For example “is the cat grey?” would be a question which falls under the question category: “color”</span></p>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Access to these granular evaluation results enables you to create meaningful visualizations of the performance of the models across various criterion, including bar and radar charts like the one below:</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"QzPuud\">\n   <div>\n    <section>\n     <figure class=\"NEBdNd\">\n      <section class=\"PBkdHd DhGbH\" jscontroller=\"SCGBie\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\">\n       <img class=\"JcsBte mZzdH ZOnyjc\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-cloudblog-publish/images/image4_1ADqbJd.max-1900x1900.png\" alt=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-cloudblog-publish/images/image4_1ADqbJd.max-1900x1900.png\" jsname=\"P3Vluc\" jsaction=\"click:HTIlC\" loading=\"lazy\">\n      </section>\n     </figure>\n     <div class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb ZpqjUe\">\n      <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n       <p>Figure 4: Visualisation of the aggregate performance of the generated media for various categories/criterion</p>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </section>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">With Gecko on Vertex AI, you gain access to a robust framework for assessing model’s capabilities at finer detail. You can refer to the </span><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/generative-ai/blob/main/gemini/evaluation/evaluate_images_with_gecko.ipynb\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" track-name=\"text- to-image\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/generative-ai/blob/main/gemini/evaluation/evaluate_images_with_gecko.ipynb\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">text- to-image</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> and </span><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/generative-ai/blob/main/gemini/evaluation/evaluate_videos_with_gecko.ipynb\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" track-name=\"text-to-video\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/generative-ai/blob/main/gemini/evaluation/evaluate_videos_with_gecko.ipynb\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">text-to-video</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> evaluation Colabs to get a first hand experience today.</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "谷歌云的 Vertex AI 推出 Gecko，一款可解释的自动化评估工具，通过基于规范的评估优化生成式媒体模型的性能。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "谷歌云的 Vertex AI 推出 Gecko，一款可解释的自动化评估工具，通过基于规范的评估优化生成式媒体模型的性能。",
  "summary": "本文介绍谷歌云 Vertex AI 上的新工具 Gecko，旨在解决评估生成式 AI 模型，特别是图像和视频生成的难题。 传统的人工评估耗时且成本高昂，而 Gecko 提供了一种基于规范、可解释且自动化的评估方法。 通过将提示语分解为语义元素，生成针对性问题，并对生成的媒体进行评分，Gecko 使开发者能够以更精细、可定制和透明的方式评估模型性能。 Gecko 通过精细化语义分析和问答生成实现可解释性评估。 本文详细介绍 Gecko 的工作原理，并提供在 Vertex AI 上使用它的步骤和代码示例。 Gecko 的应用减少了对人工评估的依赖，加速了开发周期，并提供对模型行为的深入洞察，从而有针对性地进行改进。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
